<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5064912>
    dc:description "FIGURES 47–49. Phthinomita munozae n. sp. from the ventricle (heart) of Choerodon venustus off Heron Island. 47. Adult. Lateral anteriorly, medially twisting dorso­ventrally at level of “arrow a”, ventral posteriorly, whole mount. 48. Male terminal genitalia, lateral view. 49. Female terminal genitalia, lateral view. Vitelline duct omitted as obscures path of proximal uterus. Scale­bars: 47,49, 250 m; 48, 100 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5064912/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

